hat plan harder by means of } 17... e4 $1 18. Qxe4 d3 $1 { [%csl Gd1] when Black gives up two central pawns, but in return we obtain two open files to attack the white king. After } 19. Bxd3 Bd4 $1 { White needs to be careful to avoid falling into a crushing attack. For example: } 20. Qe1 ( { But not } 20. Kc1 $2 Rhe8 21. Qg4 Re1+ 22. Rxe1 Qxe1+ 23. Qd1 Re8 $19 { and Black wins. } ) 20... Qd5 21. Kc1 Qxg2 $44 { Black has enough activity at least to regain the material. } ) 14... Bh6 $1 { By pinning the knight from the other side Black achieves an improved version compared to the game. } 15. Kb1 Nc5 16. Qe2 Bxd2 17. Qxd2 Qxd2 18. Rxd2 { Now after } 18... Ne4 $1 19. Re2 Nd6 { Black's position already seems easier. For example: } 20. f4 Nc4 $15 { [%cal Gc4e3] and with the knight coming on e3 Black has the better chances in the endgame. } *
